---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { site } from "../data/site.js";
import { breadcrumb } from "../lib/schema.js";
const nodes = [breadcrumb([{ name: "Home", path: "/" }, { name: "Contact", path: "/contact/" }])];
---
<Base
  title="Contact Kansas City Rat Control | Call 816-339-8830"
  description="Contact Kansas City Rat Control. Call 816-339-8830, answered day or night, to reach a local rat exterminator for Norway rats and mice across the KC metro."
  path="/contact/"
>
  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(nodes)} />
  <div class="page-hero"><div class="wrap">
    <p class="crumbs"><a href="/">Home</a> / Contact</p>
    <span class="kicker"><span class="dot"></span> Answered day or night</span>
    <h1>Contact Kansas City Rat Control</h1>
    <p class="lede">The fastest way to get rats handled is a phone call. Describe what you are seeing or hearing and get an honest read with an upfront estimate, no obligation.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta">
      <a class="btn-call" href={site.phoneHref}><svg><use href="#i-phone"/></svg><span>{site.phone}<small>Tap to call · Day or night</small></span></a>
    </div>
  </div></div>
  <section><div class="wrap split">
    <div class="prose-lite">
      <h2>Call for Fast, Local Rat Help</h2>
      <p>Rat and mouse problems move fast, especially once the fall cold pushes rodents indoors. A phone call is the quickest way to reach a local exterminator who can tell you what you are dealing with and what the fix takes. Have a few details ready if you can: what you have seen or heard, where in the house or yard, and how long it has been going on. That helps the exterminator size up the problem and give you an accurate, upfront estimate.</p>
      <h2>What to Mention When You Call</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>The signs.</strong> Scratching in walls, droppings, burrows, gnaw damage, or a smell.</li>
        <li><strong>The location.</strong> Attic, garage, kitchen, basement, crawlspace, or the yard.</li>
        <li><strong>The timeline.</strong> First noticed last night, or an ongoing problem across seasons.</li>
        <li><strong>The property.</strong> Older home, newer subdivision, or a commercial building.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Not sure whether it is rats or mice? That is normal, and it is exactly what a <a href="/rat-inspection-in-kansas-city/">rat inspection</a> settles. Call {site.phone} and describe it. The line is answered day or night, and you get an honest read either way.</p>
      <h2>Where We Work</h2>
      <p>Coverage runs across the whole Kansas City metro, Missouri and Kansas: Jackson, Clay, and Platte counties on the Missouri side, plus Johnson and Wyandotte in Kansas. See the full <a href="/service-areas/">service area</a> to find your city.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="callcard">
      <h3>Call Now</h3>
      <p>One call reaches a local rat exterminator. No obligation, upfront estimate.</p>
      <a class="btn-call" href={site.phoneHref}><svg><use href="#i-phone"/></svg><span>{site.phone}<small>Answered day or night</small></span></a>
      <ul>
        <li><svg><use href="#i-clock"/></svg> Answered day or night, seven days a week</li>
        <li><svg><use href="#i-check"/></svg> Rats, mice, attic cleanup, dead rat removal</li>
        <li><svg><use href="#i-pin"/></svg> Serving the KC metro, MO &amp; KS</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div></section>
</Base>
